{{BOLD}}Robot and Field setup for Skills Matches.{{/BOLD}} The {{ITALIC}}Robot{{/ITALIC}} and {{ITALIC}}Field{{/ITALIC}} are set up the same as a Teamwork Challenge {{ITALIC}}Match{{/ITALIC}}, with the following modifications: 
{{BOLD}}• {{/BOLD}}The layout of {{ITALIC}}Scoring Objects{{/ITALIC}} for a Mix & Match {{ITALIC}}Robot Skills Match{{/ITALIC}} differs from the layout for {{ITALIC}}Teamwork Challenge{{/ITALIC}} {{ITALIC}}Matches{{/ITALIC}}, as shown in Figure RSC3-1. {{ITALIC}}Pins{{/ITALIC}} and {{ITALIC}}Beams{{/ITALIC}} start in different locations on the {{ITALIC}}Field{{/ITALIC}}. The {{ITALIC}}Robot{{/ITALIC}} receives one red {{ITALIC}}Pin{{/ITALIC}} as a {{ITALIC}}Preload{{/ITALIC}}. Six {{ITALIC}}Pins{{/ITALIC}} (two red, two blue, and two orange) begin the {{ITALIC}}Match{{/ITALIC}} in the Red {{ITALIC}}Driver Station{{/ITALIC}} for {{ITALIC}}Loading{{/ITALIC}}. 
{{BOLD}}• {{/BOLD}}The blue {{ITALIC}}Load Zone{{/ITALIC}} is not used in {{ITALIC}}Robot Skills Matches{{/ITALIC}}. {{ITALIC}}Scoring Objects{{/ITALIC}} of any color may be introduced into the red {{ITALIC}}Load Zone{{/ITALIC}} only. This includes any {{ITALIC}}Scoring Object{{/ITALIC}} that is reintroduced after leaving the {{ITALIC}}Field{{/ITALIC}} during the {{ITALIC}}Match{{/ITALIC}}. 
{{BOLD}}• {{/BOLD}}The {{ITALIC}}Robot{{/ITALIC}} must be placed in contact with the structure of the red {{ITALIC}}Triangle Goal{{/ITALIC}} at the beginning of the {{ITALIC}}Match{{/ITALIC}} and after the {{ITALIC}}Robot{{/ITALIC}} is reset under rule <GG10> or <RSC5>.


